						<summary>

						<p>As the record is on the same pillar as No. 91 above (No. 230 of 1926-27) and is dated only four years later, it is assigned to the reign of <hi rend="bold">Trailōkyamalladēva (Sōmēśvara I).</hi> The object of the inscription is to confirm the grant made in No. 91 above. It is <hi rend="bold">dated Śaka 980, Viḷambi, Jyēshṭha, puṇṇame, Sunday = A.D. 1058, May 10, Sunday;</hi> ·93. The month was Adhika-Jyēshṭha.</p>						

						<p>(Published in <hi rend="italic">Ep. Ind.</hi> Vol. XV, pp. 83ff.).</p>						

						<p>The following corrections may, however, be noted in the text given here:—</p>						

